    {
      "title": "Conditional Particles and Diminutives",
      "titleArabic": "أدوات الشرط والتصغير",
      "content": [
        "Conditional particle إِذَا introduces conditions with past or future meaning. Ism al-fi'l (verbal nouns) can function like verbs. Diminutives express smallness or endearment."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "إِذَا with past verb expresses future condition",
        "Ism al-fi'l: صَهْ (be quiet!), آمِين (amen)",
        "Diminutive patterns: فُعَيْل, فُعَيْعِل",
        "Diminutive for endearment: كُلَيْب (little dog)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "إِذَا جَاءَ فَأَكْرِمْهُ", "english": "If/when he comes, honor him" },
        { "arabic": "كُتَيِّب", "english": "booklet (diminutive of كِتَاب)" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Hamzated Verbs (الفعل المهموز)",
      "titleArabic": "الفعل المهموز",
      "content": [
        "Hamzated verbs contain hamza as one of their root letters. The hamza can be in any position and follows specific rules for writing depending on the surrounding vowels."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Hamza can be first (أَخَذَ), middle (سَأَلَ), or final (قَرَأَ) radical",
        "First-hamza verbs: imperative loses hamza in some dialects",
        "Hamza spelling changes based on vowels",
        "Common verbs: أَخَذَ, أَكَلَ, سَأَلَ, قَرَأَ, بَدَأَ"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "أَخَذَ - يَأْخُذُ", "english": "to take (first-hamza)" },
        { "arabic": "سَأَلَ - يَسْأَلُ", "english": "to ask (middle-hamza)" },
        { "arabic": "قَرَأَ - يَقْرَأُ", "english": "to read (final-hamza)" }
      ]
    }
  ],
